The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
Archives
				 Mine arrest
																								Durgapur, Oct. 17: An Eastern Coalfields security officer was arrested from his official residence today in connection with the murder of assistant manager Amin Karmakar.																								Sources said a preliminary probe suggests a nexus between Ram Sevak Mishra and coal smugglers that Karmakar had been resisting. 																								S.N. Upadhyay, the chief general manager of the ECLs Kenda mining area, said: Mishra is an honest officer. 																								Karmakar was found in a paddy field with a bullet hole in his head yesterday.
